{
  "comment": "The nightly refresh contract (2026-07-14, from the external security audit; tightened by the same-day re-audit). Every requirement here must have a row in data/run-manifest.json each run — src/check-refresh.mjs enforces it in the publish gate (--manifest) and the heartbeat (--age). maxAgeDays = staleness alert threshold for the committed data (alerts fire even for EXPLAINED staleness — visibility, not blame). rows.min = catastrophic-shrink floor, set ~60-65% of the 2026-07-14 real counts; raise/lower only with a reviewed reason. Date probes: pages = oldest matching sources.json page snapshot (a lagging page is a finding); metrics/ptrDummy = the COVERAGE date, i.e. the min-th-freshest asOf (min = date.minFresh, else rows.min, else 1) — one fresh row cannot vouch for a cut whose other role cuts/specs stayed old. evidence: \"wcl\" marks requirements cross-checked against wcl-fetch/evidence.json (written by the deterministic credentialed fetch step, uploaded before the agent runs): a success row needs evidence-landed rows, not just the agent's word. wcl-dummy-raw floors were tightened to min 60 + maxAgeDays 10 on 2026-07-17 after the first verified landing (103 rows).",
  "maxRunAgeHours": 36,
  "maxRowDropPct": 0.25,
  "anomaly": { "maxTwoBandMoves": 6, "maxTotalMoves": 25 },
